# CSC350 Final Project Requirements (TaskBoard Pro)

Build and maintain a full-stack Trello-style task management web app called **TaskBoard Pro** using:

- **Next.js App Router**
- **React functional components**
- **Tailwind CSS** (Tailwind only for styling)
- **MySQL** database
- **API routes** under `app/api`

## Required course topics (must be present in the final project)

- **Dynamic routing**: `/boards/[id]`
- **React state**: `useState` for forms and UI state
- **Effects**: `useEffect` for initial data loading
- **CRUD**: full create/read/update/delete for boards and tasks
- **Forms + event handling**: create/edit flows for boards and tasks
- **Search + filtering**: real-time task search by title; filter by status
- **Loading + error states**: all data fetching should handle loading/errors
- **UI refresh after CRUD**: update UI after every mutation (re-fetch or optimistic update)

## Required pages

- `/` homepage showing all boards
- `/boards/[id]` board detail page

## Required board behavior

Each board has exactly 3 columns:

- **To Do** (`todo`)
- **In Progress** (`progress`)
- **Done** (`done`)

Tasks can be moved between columns using **buttons** (not drag-and-drop).

## Required API routes (contract)

Boards:

- `GET /api/boards`
- `POST /api/boards`
- `PUT /api/boards/[id]`
- `DELETE /api/boards/[id]`

Tasks:

- `GET /api/tasks?boardId=`
- `POST /api/tasks`
- `PUT /api/tasks/[id]`
- `DELETE /api/tasks/[id]`

## Required components

Implement and keep these components reusable (in `/components`):

- `BoardCard`
- `CreateBoardModal`
- `TaskColumn`
- `TaskCard`
- `CreateTaskModal`
- `EditTaskModal`
- `SearchBar`

## Database tables (must match)

`boards`

- `id` (INT, AUTO_INCREMENT, PRIMARY KEY)
- `title` (VARCHAR)
- `description` (TEXT)
- `created_at` (TIMESTAMP)

`tasks`

- `id` (INT, AUTO_INCREMENT, PRIMARY KEY)
- `board_id` (INT, FOREIGN KEY)
- `title` (VARCHAR)
- `description` (TEXT)
- `status` (ENUM: todo, progress, done)
- `created_at` (TIMESTAMP)

## Project structure conventions

- Pages in `/app`
- API routes in `/app/api`
- Reusable components in `/components`
- DB connection helper in `/lib/db.js` (or keep the existing project’s equivalent and document it)

## Deliverables (when requested)

When asked to “generate the entire project” or produce a complete submission, include:

- Exact folder structure
- MySQL `CREATE TABLE` statements
- Package installation commands
- `.env.local` example
- Step-by-step setup instructions
- Sample data SQL inserts

## Coding style requirements

- Beginner-friendly, clean, readable, and well-structured
- **Heavily commented** where intent is not obvious (explain *why*, not narrate trivial lines)
- Keep components small and focused; prefer clear names over cleverness
